reviewText: This isn't really a review, but as I found the product description lacking, I decided to compile this list of helpful information below. I hope this will be useful for prospective buyers to know what they're getting:OUT OF AFRICA: 1985 - 161 minutes - Director: Sydney Pollack - Starring: Meryl Streep, Robert Redford - Genre: Drama, romance - Plot: In colonial Kenya, a strong-willed baroness falls in love with a free-spirited big game hunter. PGA BEAUTIFUL MIND: 2001 - 135 minutes - Director: Ron Howard - Starring: Russell Crowe, Ed Harris, Jennifer Connelly - Genre: Drama, biography - Plot: The story of John Nash, a brilliant but asocial mathematician, and his life, love, and mental struggles. PG-13ALL QUIET ON THE WESTERN FRONT: 1930 - 136 minutes - Director: Lewis Milestone - Starring: Lew Ayres, Louis Wolheim - Genre: War, drama - Plot: A young soldier faces the soul-destroying horrors in the trenches of WWI. PGGOING MY WAY: 1944 - 126 minutes - Director: Leo McCarey- Starring: Bing Crosby, Barry Fitzgerald - Genre: Drama - Plot: A young priest challenges a struggling parish to rise to new levels of understanding. GNow let's crunch some numbers. This set costs $13.82, and contains 4 films. When we divide to find the value of the individual film you're getting, we find a cost of $3.45 per film, a good deal for this little and diverse set of award-winners. I hope this information is useful to you.
Title: Best Picture Winners Spotlight Collection
